{"key":"processedPost-25813066","value":{"id":25813066,"first":25809689,"last":25813766,"when":1550186774,"utime":"02/15/19 01:26 AM","content":"Pouring boiling water over a dry block of coir isn't going to pasteurize it.&nbsp; By the time the center of the block hydrates, the water will have cooled off below pasteurization temperature, which should be maintained for at least an hour.<br /><br />Next time, hydrate the coir first, then heat to 160F/70C at the center of the coir, and hold that temp for an hour.&nbsp; A meat thermometer is a good investment.<br />RR","title":"Re: mouldy coir - prep problems?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}